reviewText: This is another of the My Music concert series seen on PBS (and it is in color).  I found it very enjoyable and entertaining, especially Roger Williams' innovative performance of Autumn Leaves, and these concerts are of great historical value, as more and more real entertainers pass in to the next room and leave us forever.  If you enjoy the music of the fifties and family entertainment, then you will enjoy this DVD.Performances:Moments to Remember and Down By the Riverside - Four LadsHeart of My Heart and Tell Me Why - Four AcesAllegheny Moon -  Patti PageAutumn Leaves  - Roger WilliamsGraduation Day - Four FreshmanDomani and Eh Cumpari - Julius LaRosaThat's My Desire - Frankie LaineTeach Me Tonight - DeCastro SistersTry to Remember and Greenfields -Brothers FourSince I Fell for You - Lenny WelchWhen I Fall in Love - SkylinersHarbor Lights and My Prayer - Herb Reed's PlattersWhy Don't You Believe Me, My Own True love, and You Belong to Me- The DupreesBonus song: Come On-a My House - Rosemary Clooney (archival)
